caption: Great atmosphere, great drinks.
Great and chill place to get brunch
Best bar in the neighborhood
This is a wonderful restaurant and neighborhood treasure. For brunch, you bet the mimosas are fantastic.

The atmosphere there is friendly and warm. The cider there was pretty incredible. It was a white cider that had a spiced finish to it. I can't remember the name but that's maybe for the best so you can go and try it yourself!
One of my favorites. This is one of my places to meet up with friends. They have a sweet little out door space and brunch there is delicious. Always have a good time there.

Came here with a friend for food and drinks, walked in and we were not greeted or acknowledged whatsoever. Me and my friend grabbed a table and the bartender was more than aware that we were there and did not say a single word to us. There were people sitting at tables and a man at the entrance who bussed a table occasionally, and not a single employee acknowledged us. Think we made it pretty obvious that we were waiting for some sort of acknowledgement and after sitting there for over 15 minutes decided we did not want to give a business like this our money. I work in the restaurant industry as well, and my manager would rip me a new one had we treated any guest this way. 9:00pm on Saturday December 21st was time we were approximately there. To the manager of this place, please be aware of what’s going on. Not a very good look for any establishment and I truly feel offended as people who walked in after us were greeted
Great experience!

Absolutely delicious! Prices are great and it is a perfect brunch spot. Service was super nice and not pushy, which can happen in a lot of breakfast places. I had the avocado and the salmon toast, so good!
Goat talk, rank 1 brunch in bk. espn 30 for 30 presents, an actual well priced brunch with god mode food

Great brunch
IDK, doesn't this bar belong somewhere midtown or Kip's Bay? And someone should keep an ear on the music. Sometimes the section just doesn't fit the place.
Yummy reasonable brunch and nice service
I go here often for brunch on Saturdays and Sundays. Nice atmosphere and very good food. Staff is friendly and attentive.

Great food, GREAT PRICE, adorable.putdoor patio with shade, wonderful service. Cash only $15 for everything, was not any wait on a Sunday around 12 which was shocking since it's such a gem. Got crowded later on but the staff didnt rush you out. Tip well because they deserve it and you can probably afford to since it's so cheap!!
Wonderful neighborhood Irish bar with excellent whiskies and take beer.
Love this place. Weekend brunch is cheap, delicious, big portions and comes with coffee/tea and a mimosa/bloody Mary. The space is rustic and airy, staff are all really nice. NOTE: CASH ONLY.
One of the only quiet and cozy bars around with a nice backyard. No TV or loud music here. Also it's pretty dark inside and outside (sometimes too dark)
Experiment 21 IPA. Nice. Warm. Welcoming
Disappointed to learn when we got there that food wasn't served during the week.  However, bartender was very friendly and the $5 Bloody Marys were pretty darn good!!!
Best breakfast burrito I've had in nyc and at $14 for the food plus coffee and a mimosa or bloody Mary it's a killer deal.
The owner explained the family story to me, and made the food taste even better!
Met a couple of girlfriends for a cocktail to discuss an upcoming wedding for one of the girls! Service and cocktails we're fantastic
Great atmosphere and drinks.  Their brunch on the weekends is a great deal.
One of the best brunch in NYC. The only downside but not so much that is cash only so come with cash, other than that it’s great..... recommend!!!
Nice patio and good beer.

Wasn’t my favorite place for brunch. Just standard fare. The free coffee speaks for itself— I wouldn’t pay for it ever. Very burnt and bitter and had tasted like it was just sitting out for a while. Portions and price are fair.
Great little spot in East Williamsburg with a back patio
Great place for brunch! Very reasonable price and the food is delicious.
Great as Always , the bartenders are lovely and the drinks are yummy
Great all inclusive brunch.

Love their breakfast, friendliness and flexibility
Great brunch! $14 for a meal, mimosa/bloody mary/ orange juice, and coffee/tea! Good service too even if the tables are tiny.
Best 13$ Brunch in the city for sure.

Stopped in for a quick brunch, and it was great! $14 for one main, one brunch drink, and one caffeinated drink. A lot of the options looked good, but I eventually settled on the Cajun chicken sandwich. The bread, chicken, melted cheese, and caramelized onions came together beautifully and made for a great sandwich. Can't wait to come back and try some of the other things on the menu.
Patio out back is really pleasant, and the French toast is delicious!
Awesome brunch
Variety of drinks. Great brunch. Reasonable prices.
Awesome place for brunch!
I only go there for the weekend brunch. They serve brunch for $13 bucks on Saturdays and Sundays from 11am-4 I believe. Food is great!Service is great and you can’t beat the price!
Excellent brunch!

My go to Brunch spot on Sunday. With a 14 dollar per person menu(Includes 1 drink) there is no place that comes close. Food is amazing, and drinks are even better. Try the bloody Mary for sure. Wait times are not bad either, especially on Sundays when they are super busy.
The best brunch in NY state. Great food, amazing staff, even have a patio for summer days.
great brunch menu
Cash only - not a legitimate bar.  We got tied up in their accounting bureaucracy, having to close our tab and open a new one at 4pm because some person happened to be leaving.
Awesome friendly pub one of my favourites in the neighborhood for years....

Was there for brunch on a Sunday morning. Were seated immediately, although 30 minutes later the place was packed. Staff was very attentive and very nice. Food arrived soon after ordered, the plates were loaded. Food was fabulous. Lots of families with young children made the place even more enjoyable. We will definitely return to Harefield Road!
Chill bar with a relaxed atmosphere, bartender was friendly and the drinks are good!
Brunch Sat was great

Good place to grab brunch off of the Graham L stop. The food isn't anything to write home about but the meals come with a coffee and a bloody/mimosa. The prices on their website don't reflect the current pricing. At the time of my last visit it was $15 for the brunch special. Great outdoor patio when it's nice out.
Amazing brunch. Nice homey vibe with great service. Felt like being back in Ireland!
A very basic dish of huevos rancheros turned out to be one of the best if not the best I have ever had

Solid brunch if a bit plain. Not a lot of surprises to be found.
Awesome affordable brunch. Lovely service as well.
Cool brunch place with good food, very nice staff, great portions, and even an outdoor space. $14 for good food + coffee + Bloody Mary = perfect!
Love that you can bring your dog. Quite, cash only.
I like drink beers always

Amazing brunch. Quick service. Great prices! Quality isn’t lost in casual dining experience.

I went here a few times with my cousin and it's a different issue everytime I go. She got wine that tasted disgusting and I got a cocktail that wasn't made properly. The same thing happened the other three times we went. I do not recommend this place at all.
Cash only. Plan ahead. Staff is phenomenal.
Delicious brunch, loved the included mimosa!!
Great brunch special here & good service too
The day I went they weren't serving food which was kind of disappointing. Also the lighting is really dark for my taste.
Absolutely amazing service. Great steak and eggs!
Cheap brunch, free mimosa, huevos rancheros is usually hit or miss but this place does it right. Bonus points for the cute outdoor space. Looks like they have amazing happy hour pricing as well.
Love this place. Cash only!

Read the reviews and was super excited to try the Bloody Mary's and food. Got the eggs Benedict that came out without holendaze and served with French friend. The Bloody tasted like cheap watered down vodka. Didn't eat or drink my meal, paid and left.
My favorite place for brunch!!!

Love the Irish bartender
Brunchy brunch brunch face brunch
Has everything you need in a bar and nothing else. Low d@uche factor, decent prices.
Delicious food and amazing service ❤️ nice for a boozy brunch!
A great dive bar where you can get a proper pour of Guinness, good selection of whiskey. The grilled cheese sandwiches are also KILLER
Solid, modern pub. Backyard patio.
Horrible brunch service. Just don't do it. This please is getting worse and worse.
Pretty basic bar with a nice beer selection. A great location in a pretty bare neighborhood between Brooklyn Steel and the station.
This is one of my favorite brunch spots! For $13 you get a cocktail, coffee, and a meal! Great atmosphere and staff! Can't beat it for the price.

Harefield Road is a great place to have a a beer during night or have a brunch in the morning. Their 14 dollar brunch is great value and very tasty. I was disappointed once by their egg benedicts but they refreshed the menu and took them off recently!  Staff is always friendly and the place is never too crowded.

This is my favorite go to bar. Brunch is awesome and consistent. Everything is delicious.  The staff aren't the warmest but the service is great. Beer, wine, and whiskey selection is great. Nice bar with dive bar prices. Neighbor hood staple.
Excellent! $13 brunch menu, friendly staff and great food.
Always the best brunch
Cool spot.

Love the atmosphere
Great Irish Bar, and an amazing place to grab Brunch.
Great brunch for $13!
It was nice and cozy.  Brunch was tasty, and was a good deal for $13 that comes with a mimosa and coffee.  A bit slow service, but I'd definitely recommend.
One of the remaining great local neighborhood bars in the neighborhood.
Great pub, huge drink selection and wonderful staff.
Wonderful brunch place with friendly staff and a sunny and calm backyard. We'll come back!
Great bartenders. Good music. Decent selection.
Cool spot with friendly staff and a good happy hour deal
Amazing food the only regret is the menu doesn't have much to choose from.
Very cute place, would have never known it was there if it wasn't for a local telling us about it! Food is great, definitely a must try place!
Probably can't beat the brunch price here but we waited a while and they weren't too friendly
Super cheap brunch. For $13 you can get a bloody mary or mimosa, and your choice of an entree. The menu was decent sized and everything was good.
They have great vegetarian options!
$6 taps and a great whiskey list. Cash only. Nice wooden bar with a friendly barkeep. What more do you need?

Great weekend brunch place! Only $13 for mimosa or bellini, free refill of coffee or tea, and brunch entree. Had the Harefied Eggs Benedict - had a bit of a kick to it. They don't take reservations, and sometimes have a wait, but worth it!
Friendly bartenders, open, clean space if not that cozy.
Best bunch deal in the area. Cash only and you'll only be seated once your whole party has arrived. The owner is frequently there and runs a great operation. Bar is a lot of fun, too
Been here for brunch many times over the past year. A great little cheap brunch spot ($12 for food and a drink). Their challah french toast is amazing! Haven't had a bad thing on the menu.
My favourite bar in this whole city. Great range of whiskys and bourbons at very fair prices. Throw into the mix very friendly staff in a cosy wooden atmosphere.  This place has never disappointed.
Brunch here is always on point!

Went here for brunch on a Sunday. There was no wait which was great, considering brunch spots get packed quickly on Sundays. The food was good. I had the eggs benedict while my friend had the grilled chicken sandwich (which was actually pretty amazing). Ambience is typical and fitting for the Williamsburg scene. There's a decent amount of outdoor seating as well - good perk!
Awesome burrito Orgasm in my belly Great 12 dollar brunch
This place is the jam. $12 brunch on the weekends including coffee and a mimosa or Bloody Mary with food. The breakfast burrito is like putting a little piece of heaven into your belly.

Harefield Road is ALL right. Went here for brunch and the food is decent. In terms of deliciousness and ambience you can probably do better something better at your corner deli and if you drank your own bottle of Andre on your couch.  That would probably make for a better experience. But if you're going to come here and hang out with your friends that's fine. I just wouldn't WAIT that's all.  Service was friendly, but kinda slow. Food is inexpensive.  It's a little dark, cause it's really a pub that has a brunch open on weekends for the people who live out here.  Had the burger. Pretty good. Home fries a little mushy. Bloody mary is mostly mix, but not unbearably vinegar-y at least. I mean. It's just A-OK.

This is one of my favorite brunch spots in NYC! A block away from the L train off Graham Ave makes it an easy access spot for friends from different boroughs to brunch at. Bring CASH as it's a CASH ONLY spot, but not to worry this bang-for-your-buck ($12) includes your meal, choice of tea or coffee AND a mimosa or bloody mary. With $20 you brunch, grab yourself another mimosa and still leave a decent tip! Happy Brunching!
Best deal for brunch in the neighborhood. The food is great and it's only $12 which includes a drink. They have outdoor seating in the back.
Great portions for brunch. It is very popular so there is always a line but it usually goes fast. The food is great also so come hungry.
Gets a bit crazy on weekend mornings for brunch, but it's an awesome place. Friendly staff, awesome beer selection. Very dark and intimate - it's like a cave even in the middle of the day.

This is probably one of the most popular brunch spots in Williamsburg because it's a really good deal. $12 for a meal and a free alcoholic drink. Get there early unless you don't mind waiting for hours for some breakfast.

I've never had a corner bar to call my own in NY after 20 years of living here, so I was pretty surprised when HF became that bar. The staff is amazing, there's a great back patio, the crowd is diverse and friendly, and it's pretty much ruined beer selection for me  - every time I go to a Manhattan bar now and there's no IPA on tap I curse HF for turning me in to a beer snob. Brunch is also great - and comes with a drink.

Can't speak to the food, but overall it's a nice bar with a good selection. Warm, inviting old wood interior. The back porch is pleasant, if a little stark. Occasionally the host live music which is a nice touch.
Other than the crap veggie burger, it's pretty good.
great, relaxed hangout with a cozy interior, good drinks, and a backyard patio.
